				<td colspan="2"><span>Aggro range is monstrous.
<br />
Usual thing I'd do was to zone in, zoom up to northwest corner, Fade.  This would clear most things, but would still end up with a couple of spiders close by that would jump in as soon as I was least ready for them.  In the end, I just accepted that I was going to have to clear the break in mobs before starting on the Amy's.  Once I accepted this, wasn't too bad.  At 65, it was usually a standard swarm kite, without being too bothered if I didn't break charm before they died (there for amy whip, not loot!).  20-30 mins of this and I was then ready for the proper Amy Warrior pulling.  Having the cleared area made it alot easier todo what I was there todo, and even if the odd thing did wander by, CharmBurn time again!
<br />
I started to get the hang of it in the end (took 6-7 solo fear raids before I got the whip), and although I think it might be possible todo earlier, I can't overstate how usefull hitting 65 for better resists and having FM was.
<br />

<br />
Jyve AFK</span></td>
